[SAY] Back in the middle. B for backward, F for forward.
[SAY] One gotcha. If you use T mux, control B is the T mux prefix key. T mux intercepts it before Vim sees it. Most people remap the T mux prefix to control space to fix that.
[SAY] Control B. Page up. A full screen at a time.